{{Infobox language |name=Chashan |nativename=Echang |states=[[China]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |speakers=587 |date=2010 |ref=<ref>Dai Qingxia [戴庆厦] (2010). ''The Chashan people of Pianma and their language'' [片马茶山人及其语言]. Beijing: The Commercial Press [商务印书馆].</ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Burmish languages|Burmish]] |fam5=Maruic |iso3=none |iso3comment=(included in {{ethnolink|lsi}}) |glotto=none |glottorefname= }}
'''Chashan 茶山''' (autonym: ''{{IPA|ŋɔ˧˩ tʃʰaŋ˥}}'') is a [[Burmish languages|Burmish]] language spoken in Pianma Township 片马镇, [[Lushui County]], Yunnan, China, in Xiapianma 下片马,<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=57081</ref> Gangfang 岗房,<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=57071</ref> and Gulang 古浪<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=57070</ref> villages (Dai, et al. 2009).<ref>[http://docs.china-europa-forum.net/a___________1.pdf 片马茶山人和谐的多语生活]</ref> It is closely related to [[Lashi language|Lashi]], and has 56.3% lexical similarity with Lashi of [[Lushui County]] out of a sample of 1,000 vocabulary words (Dai 2010:118).
In Pianma Township, there are 587 Chashan people officially classified as ethnic [[Lisu people|Lisu]]. The local people consider the Chashan to be a distinct ethnic group, separate from the [[Jingpo people]] ({{zh|景颇族}}). The Chashan autonym is ''{{IPA|ŋɔ˧˩ tʃʰaŋ˥}}'' (Echang 峨昌), similar to that of the [[Achang language|Achang]]. More Chashan speakers may be found across the border in [[Kachin State]], [[Burma]].
