'''Rumpology''', '''Asstrology''' or '''bottom reading''' is a [[pseudoscience]] akin to [[physiognomy]], performed by examining crevices, dimples, warts, moles and folds of a person's [[buttocks]] in much the same way a [[chirology|chirologist]] would read the palm of the [[hand]].<ref name="skepdic2">{{cite web|url=http://www.skepdic.com/essays/rumpology4dummies.html|title=Rumplogy for Dummies|first=Robert Todd|last=Carrol|publisher=The Skeptic's Dictionary}}</ref>
==History== The term ''rumpology'' is a [[neologism]]. The American astrologer [[Jackie Stallone]] claims that rumpology is known to have been practiced in ancient times by the [[Babylonia]]ns, the [[History of India|Indians]], and the [[Ancient Greeks]] and [[Ancient Rome|Romans]],<ref name="stallone">{{cite web |url=http://www.jacquelinestallone.com/rumps.html |title=Jacqueline Stallone's Rumpology Reports! |accessdate=2007-06-05}}</ref> although she provides no evidence for this claim. Stallone has been largely responsible for the supposed "revival" of rumpology in modern times.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}
==Theory and practice== Rumpologists have a variety of theories as to the meaning of different posterior characteristics. According to Stallone, the left and right buttocks reveal a person's past and future, respectively, although she has also commented that "The crack of your behind corresponds to the division of the two hemispheres of the brain".<ref name="Salon">{{cite web |url=http://www.salon.com/1999/09/13/monnp/ |title=This is Sly's mom on crack |publisher=Salon.com |first=Amy |last=Reiter |date=September 13, 1999}}</ref> According to blind German [[clairvoyant]] and rumpologist Ulf Beck, an "apple-shaped, muscular bottom indicates someone who is charismatic, dynamic, very confident and often creative. A person who enjoys life. A pear-shaped bottom suggests someone very steadfast, patient and down-to-earth."<ref name="tatters">{{cite news |first= Nick |last= Tattersall |authorlink= |title= Blind Psychic Gropes Buttocks to See Future |url= http://soundingcircle.com/newslog2.php/__show_article/_a000195-000303.htm |work= Sounding Circle |publisher= Reuters |id= |pages= |page= |date= July 9, 2003 |accessdate= 2007-04-25 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070708231912/http://soundingcircle.com/newslog2.php/__show_article/_a000195-000303.htm |archivedate= July 8, 2007 |df= }}</ref> The [[British people|British]] rumpologist Sam Amos also uses shape to diagnose personality,<ref name="sun">{{cite news|title=Ass-tronomy|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/features/2507600/What-does-your-bum-shape-say-about-you-We-find-out.html|work=[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]|date=June 30, 2009|location=London|first=Kate|last=Jackson}}</ref> and claims that "A round bottom indicates the person is open, happy and optimistic in life. However, a flat bottom suggests the person is rather vain and is negative and sad."<ref name="metro">{{cite web|title=Have a rumpologist read your bottom|url=http://www.metro.co.uk/lifestyle/article.html?Have_a_rumpologist_read_your_bottom&in_article_id=459128&in_page_id=194|date=January 5, 2009|publisher=[[Metro (Associated Metro Limited)|Metro]]}}</ref>
Rumpology can be performed either by sight, touch or by using buttock prints.<ref name="stallone"/> In addition to live readings, Jackie Stallone will perform buttock readings using e-mailed digital photographs,<ref name="skepdic1"/> and has claimed to predict the outcome of Presidential elections and Oscar awards by reading the bottoms of her two pet [[Doberman Pinscher]]s.<ref name="Salon2">{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2001/03/21/npwed_37/ |title=Streisand: Stallone's mom's butt prints are hot! |first=Amy |last=Reiter |publisher=Salon.com |date=March 21, 2001}}</ref> Ulf Buck claims he can read people's futures by feeling their naked buttocks.<ref name="tatters"/>
==Criticism== Upon learning about a TV show 'rumpologist' known as Professor Jose Miranda (a pupil of Stallone's<ref name="skepdic1">{{cite web |url=http://www.skepdic.com/rumpology.html |title=rumpology |publisher=[[The Skeptic's Dictionary]]}}</ref>), the Florida psychic [[Sheree Silver]] disassociated herself from the practice, telling the ''[[Sun-Sentinel]]'', "I can't imagine anyone wasting their time and money on someone like this when there are so many legitimate psychics out there."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.book-of-thoth.com/article1014.html |title=Psychic TV `rumpologist' becomes huge hit on Spanish-language TV |publisher=The Book Of THoTH |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911010556/http://www.book-of-thoth.com/article1014.html |archivedate=2011-09-11 |df= }}</ref>
