{{Infobox writer | name = Trygve Kristofer Knudsen | image = Trygve_Knudsen.jpg | birth_date = 23 June 1897 | birth_place = {{flag|Norway|1899}} [[Tønsberg]] | death_date = 18 January 1968 (70) | death_place = {{flag|Norway}} [[Oslo]] | occupation = [[philologist]], [[professor]], [[linguist]], [[lexicographer]] }}
'''Trygve Knudsen''' (23 June 1897 &ndash; 18 January 1968) was a [[Norwegian people|Norwegian]] [[philologist]], [[linguist]] and [[lexicographer]].
==Personal life== Knudsen was born in [[Tønsberg]] as the son of lawyer Knud Peder Knudsen (1863&ndash;1937) and Henriette von Lachmann Mørck (1867&ndash;1923). He married Grethe Tønnessen in 1925.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Trygve Knudsen |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]] |first=Tove |last=Bull |authorlink=Tove Bull |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Trygve_Knudsen/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=10 April 2009}}</ref>
==Career== Knudsen [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in Tønsberg 1916, and enrolled in [[philology]] at the [[University of Oslo|University of Kristiania]]. He took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in 1923, and his thesis was issued as a book, titled ''P. A. Munch og samtidens norske målstræv''. Between 1925 and 1930 he worked as a University [[research fellow]], and later as a teacher in [[Aker, Norway|Aker]] and [[Oslo]]. From 1935 he worked as a teacher at [[Oslo katedralskole|Oslo Cathedral School]], until 1946, when he started lecturing at the University. He was appointed professor at the [[University of Oslo]] in 1954, and kept this position until he retired in 1967.<ref name=nbl/>
Knudsen was co-editor of the dictionary ''[[Norsk Riksmålsordbok]]'' from 1925, together with [[Alf Sommerfelt]], who had started the work in 1922.<ref name=nro-I>{{cite book |chapter=Innledning |author1=Alf Sommerfelt |author2=Trygve Knudsen |author3=Harald Noreng |author4=Ragnar Ullmann | year=1991 |origyear=1957|pages=III-IX |title=[[Norsk Riksmålsordbok]] |language=Norwegian |volume=1 |editor1=Trygve Knudsen |editor2=Alf Sommerfelt |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget }}</ref><ref name=nbl-sommerfelt>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Alf Sommerfelt |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]] |first=Even Hebbe |last=Johnsrud |editor=Helle, Knut | publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Alf_Sommerfelt/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=10 April 2009}}</ref> The first parts of the dictionary were published in 1930, and the dictionary work was completed in 1957.<ref name=nbl/> After publishing the dictionary, the editors started working on a supplementary volume. As Sommerfelt died in 1965, and Knudsen died in 1968, their work was completed by [[Harald Noreng]], who also had been co-editor of volume four of the dictionary. The two supplementary volumes of ''Norsk Riksmålsordbok'' (labeled V and VI) were issued in 1995.<ref name=nbl-noreng>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Harald Noreng|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]] |first=Asbjørn |last=Aarseth |authorlink=Asbjørn Aarseth |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] | publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Harald_Noreng/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=10 April 2009}}</ref><ref name=nro-V>{{cite book |chapter=Innledning |first= Harald |last=Noreng |year=1995 |pages=III-IX |title=[[Norsk Riksmålsordbok]] |language=Norwegian |volume=5 |editor=Trygve Knudsen |editor2=Alf Sommerfelt |editor3=Harald Noreng |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget }}</ref><ref name=snl-nro>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Norsk Riksmålsordbok |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |editor=Henriksen, Petter |url=http://www.snl.no/Norsk_Riksmålsordbok |language=Norwegian | accessdate=10 April 2009 }}</ref>
Knudsen was co-editor of the magazine ''Maal og Minne'' from 1951. He wrote the book ''Gammelnorsk Homiliebok'' in 1952. He was chairman for the [[Norwegian Language Council|Norwegian Language Committee]] (''Norsk Språknemnd'') from 1956 to 1957. He wrote articles on city dialects in general, and more specifically on dialects in Oslo and Tønsberg. He was a radio speaker, especially on the subject "Norwegian language", and he held guest lectures at the universities of [[University of Bergen|Bergen]], [[Lund University|Lund]], [[Uppsala University|Uppsala]] and [[Göteborg University|Göteborg]]. He was also a literary critic.<ref name=nbl/>
Knudsen received an [[honorary degree]] at the [[University of Stockholm]] in 1960.<ref name=nbl/>
