{{Infobox language |name=Uma’ Lasan |altname= |nativename= |states=[[Malaysia]], [[Indonesia]] |region=[[Borneo]] |ethnicity= |speakers={{sigfig|5,750|1}} |date=1981–2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[North Bornean languages|North Bornean]] |fam4=[[North Sarawakan languages|North Sarawakan]] |fam5=[[Kenyah languages|Kenyah]] |lc1=xky |ld1= Uma’ Lasan ([[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]] |lc2=ulu |ld2= Uma’ Lung ([[East Kalimantan]], [[Indonesia]]) |glotto=uppe1425 |glottorefname=Upper Pujungan }}
'''Uma’ Lasan''' (Western Kenyah) is a [[Kayan languages|Kayan language]] of [[Borneo]]. '''Uma’ Lung''' is marginally intelligible with the other varieties.
